# Intercâmbio acadêmico com SARC

O Programa de pós-graduação em Música da UFBA e o grupo de pesquisa
Genos promovem um intercâmbio acadêmico com o Sonic Arts Research
Center (SARC), da Queen's University, de Belfast.

Data: 6/4/9
Local: GenosLab

Programação:

 16:00-17:00 - Palestra do prof. Pedro Rebelo.
   - Apresentação dos trabalhos recentes realizados no SARC
   - Apresentação da comuncação "Dramaturgias Musicais na Net"

 17:00-17:30 - Interação informal com interessados em bolsa de
estudos para o SARC*

 19:00-20:00 - Recital de música eletroacústica com o prof. Pedro Rebelo


* - Sonic Arts Research Centre announces collaboration with Brazilian
Universities

The Sonic Arts Research Centre at Queen's University Belfast is
extremely pleased to announce a PhD studentship sponsored by Banco
Santander with a view to developing links between Queen's and
Universities in Brazil. The studentships is fully funded for three
years and is open to Brazilian nationals of high calibre working in
the field of sonic arts and music technology. In addition SARC is
opening an exchange for MA students in Sonic Arts and related areas.

Applications on all areas of sonic arts are welcome. For more
information on SARC's ongoing research and events in Brasil during
April 2009 please visit www.sarc.qub.ac.uk

For more information please contact Dr Pedro Rebelo, (P.Rebelo@qub.ac.uk)

